The greater bandicoot rat (Bandicota indica) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Bangladesh, China, India, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Nepal, Sri Lanka, Taiwan, Thailand, and Vietnam. It can grow to about 27â€“29 cm without including the tail which tail can grow to 28 cm. These should not be confused with true bandicoots which are marsupials inhabiting Australia and neighbouring New Guinea.
